SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 813
By Watson
A RESOLUTION to recognize and congratulate Erik and Amanda
Niel upon the naming of their Chattanooga
restaurants to the MICHELIN Guide American
South.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should recognize those exemplary local businesses and
their proprietors who, through their unwavering commitment to excellence, are a credit to this
State; and
WHEREAS, Chattanooga restaurateurs Erik and Amanda Niel recently earned global
recognition for their culinary excellence with the naming of three of their restaurants to the
inaugural MICHELIN Guide American South selection of elite Southern restaurants; and
WHEREAS, the 2025 MICHELIN Guide American South is the first regional edition of
the MICHELIN Guide in North America; the inaugural selection covers Alabama, Louisiana,
Mississippi, North Carolina, South Carolina, Tennessee, and the pre-existing Atlanta Guide; and
WHEREAS, Little Coyote, Easy Bistro, and Main Street Meats, all owned and operated
by the Niels, were named to this prestigious collection; and
WHEREAS, Little Coyote, located at 3950 Tennessee Avenue, was given the Bib
Gourmand distinction, which recognizes eateries offering great food at a great value; and
WHEREAS, Easy Bistro, located at 801 Chestnut Street, along with Main Street Meats,
located at 217 East Main Street, were named Recommended restaurants; and
WHEREAS, these honors shine a spotlight on the Niels, who have elevated
Chattanooga's food culture into something deliciously special—a diverse, innovative culinary
scene that enhances quality of life for residents and creates memorable experiences for visitors;
and
SJR0813
012697
- 1 -

WHEREAS, recognition in the MICHELIN Guide American South selection validates
what locals have known for years—that Chattanooga offers exceptional dining experiences
worthy of international acclaim; and
WHEREAS, Erik and Amanda Niel have contributed greatly to the culinary experience of
restaurant goers in Chattanooga, and it is most fitting that they be honored on this special
occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize owners Erik and Amanda Niel on the
selection of Little Coyote, Easy Bistro, and Main Street Meats to the MICHELIN Guide American
South, extending our best wishes for every continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
